            {
              "enText": "<b>Lesson 13 • Discussing A Mistake</b>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "Chris and Todd work for Alpine Design, a furniture manufacturer. When Todd accidentally orders the wrong amount of wood, his boss Chris warns him to be more careful in the future."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Chris:</b> Todd, we got our shipment of wood yesterday. We're short by 18 tons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Todd:</b> Our wood supplier must've made mistake. I could've sworn that I ordered the right amount."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Chris:</b> You'd better go back and double-check your order."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Todd:</b> Oops, you're right. I accidentally ordered two tons instead of twenty. No big deal. I'll just put in another order."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Chris:</b> When filling out order forms, you need to dot your i's and cross your t's. You shouldn't be making careless mistakes like this."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Todd::</b> I just forgot to add a zero after the two. Don't make a mountain out of a molehill. No need to blow things out of proportion."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Chris:</b> This is very serious. Now we won't have enough wood to finish the furniture order we got from La-Z Boy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Todd::</b> Okay, sorry I dropped the ball."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "enText": "<b>Chris:</b> Todd, this may be a bitter pill to swallow, but your work lately hasn't been up to scratch. You've really been asleep at the wheel!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
